comments: Ivey (DET) is drawn into the air by the pump fake towards Thompson (GSW) and initiates illegal body contact that affects his jump shot attempt.
Jackson-Davis (GSW) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Duren (DET) moves laterally into Curry (GSW) and initiates body contact that affects his SQBR.
Duren (DET) establishes screening position in Kuminga's (GSW) path and marginal contact occurs to his side as the pick is set.
Thompson (GSW) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Cunningham (DET) prior to incidental arm contact occurring during the drive.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Ivey's (DET) pass goes out of bounds.
Bogdanovic (DET) lifts and re-plants his pivot foot prior to releasing his dribble.
Thompson (GSW) maintains a legal guarding position as he moves alongside Bogdanovic's (DET) path and makes clean contact with the ball during the contest of Bogdanovic's driving shot attempt.
Jackson-Davis (GSW) brings his hands toward Ivey (DET) and marginal contact occurs as Jackson-Davis releases away to roll to the basket.

Duren (DET) reaches across and initiates some contact with Jackson-Davis's (GSW) head as he secures the rebound.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Burks (DET) reaches in and marginal contact occurs with Curry's (GSW) right arm on the perimeter.
Burks (DET) briefly places a hand on Curry's (GSW) back and immediately removes it.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Curry (GSW) touches the ball last before going out of bounds.
Saric (GSW) extends both hands forward and initiates body contact with Cunningham (DET) during the drive that affects his SQBR.  The illegal contact occurs before Cunningham's shooting motion.
Ivey (DET) hooks his arm around Curry (GSW) in order to gain leverage during the drive to the basket.
Ivey (DET) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of a defensive goaltending by Jackson-Davis (GSW) is confirmed.
Duren (DET) immediately slides his hand off of Curry's (GSW) side and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
